Description: Egypt, view of large ruined stone building [temple?] at Luxor. Reliefs representing adults [male?] on building. Large stone figure representing adult male leader/ruler, "Ramesses", wearing head-dress, in front of building. Medium: Gelatin silver print.
Producer name: Photographed by: John Frederick Clifford Hunt
Curator's comments: Reliefs would have been painted in the past. J M Hudson, 27/01/1998. Geography: Identity of Ramses suggested by J M Hudson, 27/01/1998. Circumstances: The Imperial War Museum holds photographs from the same collection with a more military content - see [HUN-] PIC DOC 66.
